    # Project Rules

    Before creating or modifying any UI components, ALWAYS reference design-system.md.

    Use ONLY CSS variables defined in globals.css. No hardcoded values.

    When using Tailwind:

    - Use arbitrary values to reference CSS vars: `bg-[var(--color-primary)]`
    - Or use custom component classes defined in globals.css
    - NEVER use arbitrary Tailwind values (no p-7, no text-gray-650)
    - NEVER hardcode colors (no #3b82f6, no rgb values)

    Dark mode is handled automatically via CSS variables in globals.css - do not add manual dark: variants.

    When creating reusable component patterns, add them to globals.css using @apply in the @layer components section.

    ## Content Management

    ALL text content must be separated from components and stored in src/data/.

    Structure:

    - Global content (nav, footer): `src/data/navigation.ts`, `src/data/footer.ts`
    - Page content: `src/data/pages/[pagename].ts` where the object structure mirrors the page structure

    Example:

    ```ts
    // src/data/pages/home.ts
    export const homeContent = {
    hero: { title: "...", subtitle: "..." },
    cta: { heading: "...", button: "..." },
    features: { heading: "...", items: [...] },
    }
    ```

    - NEVER hardcode text strings in components
    - Import page content: `import { homeContent } from '@/data/pages/home'`
    - Pass sections to components: `<Hero content={homeContent.hero} />`
    -Import data files directly in components - no prop passing for content. Avoid unnecessary interface typing for content props.

## Interaction & Animation

- Simple UI toggles may use native HTML semantics (e.g. <details>) where appropriate.
- If an interaction requires:

  - custom enter/exit animations
  - height or layout animations
  - coordinated open/close behavior
  - or future extensibility beyond basic toggling

  THEN prefer React-managed state using hooks (useState, useEffect).

- In such cases:

  - Mark components as "use client"
  - Use React state to control interaction
  - Drive animations via CSS classes, data-attributes, or animation libraries

Do not refactor, restructure, or modify any code that I have personally added or changed unless I explicitly instruct you to do so.
